SECTION 5 — Human Settlements: Definition, Types, Classification
From hamlet to mega-city — complete classification
5.1 Definition of Settlement
A settlement is any form of human habitation — ranging from a single dwelling to a large city — where
people live and carry out their activities permanently or semi-permanently. Settlements are characterised
by location, site, situation, function, pattern, and size.
