SECTION 7 — Rural Settlements
Features, types, issues and Indian context
7.1 Definition
Rural settlements are areas where the majority of the population is engaged in primary activities
(agriculture, fishing, forestry, mining). They are characterised by low population density, close proximity to
natural environments, and strong community bonds.
