7.3 Environmental Issues in Rural Settlements
• Groundwater depletion — over-extraction for irrigation (especially in Punjab-Haryana)
• Soil degradation — overuse of chemical fertilisers, monoculture farming
• Deforestation — for agricultural expansion and fuelwood
• Agrochemical pollution — pesticides contaminating soil and water
• Indoor air pollution — use of biomass (cow dung, wood) for cooking ® respiratory diseases
• Lack of sanitation — open defecation pollutes water bodies (Swachh Bharat Mission addresses this)
• Climate vulnerability — directly dependent on rain-fed agriculture ® drought, flood impacts
